#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:6
msgid "How to implement xunit-style set-up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:8
msgid ""
"This section describes a classic and popular way how you can implement "
"fixtures (setup and teardown test state) on a per-module/class/function "
"basis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:14
msgid ""
"While these setup/teardown methods are simple and familiar to those coming "
"from a ``unittest`` or ``nose`` background, you may also consider using "
"pytest's more powerful :ref:`fixture mechanism <fixture>` which leverages "
"the concept of dependency injection, allowing for a more modular and more "
"scalable approach for managing test state, especially for larger projects "
"and for functional testing.  You can mix both fixture mechanisms in the same "
"file but test methods of ``unittest.TestCase`` subclasses cannot receive "
"fixture arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:26
msgid "Module level setup/teardown"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:28
msgid ""
"If you have multiple test functions and test classes in a single module you "
"can optionally implement the following fixture methods which will usually be "
"called once for all the functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:32
msgid ""
"def setup_module(module):\n"
"    \"\"\"setup any state specific to the execution of the given module."
"\"\"\"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def teardown_module(module):\n"
"    \"\"\"teardown any state that was previously setup with a setup_module\n"
"    method.\n"
"    \"\"\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:43
msgid "As of pytest-3.0, the ``module`` parameter is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:46
msgid "Class level setup/teardown"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:48
msgid ""
"Similarly, the following methods are called at class level before and after "
"all test methods of the class are called:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:51
msgid ""
"@classmethod\n"
"def setup_class(cls):\n"
"    \"\"\"setup any state specific to the execution of the given class "
"(which\n"
"    usually contains tests).\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@classmethod\n"
"def teardown_class(cls):\n"
"    \"\"\"teardown any state that was previously setup with a call to\n"
"    setup_class.\n"
"    \"\"\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:69
msgid "Method and function level setup/teardown"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:71
msgid ""
"Similarly, the following methods are called around each method invocation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:73
msgid ""
"def setup_method(self, method):\n"
"    \"\"\"setup any state tied to the execution of the given method in a\n"
"    class.  setup_method is invoked for every test method of a class.\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def teardown_method(self, method):\n"
"    \"\"\"teardown any state that was previously setup with a setup_method\n"
"    call.\n"
"    \"\"\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:86
msgid "As of pytest-3.0, the ``method`` parameter is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:88
msgid ""
"If you would rather define test functions directly at module level you can "
"also use the following functions to implement fixtures:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:91
msgid ""
"def setup_function(function):\n"
"    \"\"\"setup any state tied to the execution of the given function.\n"
"    Invoked for every test function in the module.\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def teardown_function(function):\n"
"    \"\"\"teardown any state that was previously setup with a "
"setup_function\n"
"    call.\n"
"    \"\"\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:104
msgid "As of pytest-3.0, the ``function`` parameter is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:106
msgid "Remarks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:108
msgid ""
"It is possible for setup/teardown pairs to be invoked multiple times per "
"testing process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:111
msgid ""
"teardown functions are not called if the corresponding setup function "
"existed and failed/was skipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:114
msgid ""
"Prior to pytest-4.2, xunit-style functions did not obey the scope rules of "
"fixtures, so it was possible, for example, for a ``setup_method`` to be "
"called before a session-scoped autouse fixture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/xunit_setup.rst:118
msgid ""
"Now the xunit-style functions are integrated with the fixture mechanism and "
"obey the proper scope rules of fixtures involved in the call."
msgstr ""
